---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Hestan Refrigerator Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Hestan refrigerator repair across SoCal, column built-in, Bordeaux/Matte finishes, Anaheim CA HQ. Meyer-backed luxury built down the freeway. $89 dx.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/hestan-refrigerator-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Hestan sounds Italian, is it actually from Italy?",
    a: "Nope, and that's one of the most common misconceptions we hear on the phone. Hestan is a California company, founded in 2014 by Stanley Cheng (a cookware-industry veteran, the same Stanley Cheng behind Anolon and Circulon), with its headquarters and 70,000-square-foot manufacturing facility in Anaheim, California, roughly a 45-minute drive down the freeway from our Los Angeles branch. The Italian-sounding name was a deliberate brand-positioning choice, not a heritage claim. Hestan is a subsidiary of Meyer Corporation, the US cookware conglomerate that also owns Anolon, Circulon, Farberware, and KitchenAid cookware. Practically for service: Hestan is genuinely made in LA-adjacent California, the Anaheim facility houses manufacturing, engineering, the test kitchen, and the certified test lab. When our techs service a Hestan unit, we're working on a product built 45 miles from where the repair is happening. That's unusual enough in luxury appliances that it's worth stating straight."
  },
  {
    q: "Is Hestan Commercial the same company as Hestan residential? We have the grill and are thinking about the fridge.",
    a: "Same company, same Anaheim facility, same engineering team. Stanley Cheng founded Hestan Commercial in 2014 with a focus on professional commercial cooking suites (specifically the Hestan Commercial line designed with chef input from Thomas Keller and Timothy Hollingsworth), and the residential line, including outdoor grills launched in 2016 and indoor appliances including the Hestan column refrigerator, grew out of the same operation. There's no sub-brand split between Hestan Commercial and Hestan Residential the way some brands separate their scope; it's all one company, one service network, one parts chain. Aspire by Hestan, that's the separate sibling brand (mainstream price tier, positioned below Hestan's luxury line). If you have a Hestan outdoor grill in Pacific Palisades and you're considering the Hestan column fridge for the kitchen, brand-family consistency is genuinely real here: same designer palette (Bordeaux, Matte Black, Matte White, Froth, Tin), same trim hardware finishes available, same service team."
  },
  {
    q: "Our kitchen designer specified the Hestan column refrigerator, what makes it different from Sub-Zero or Thermador at this price point?",
    a: "Three real differences our techs point to when clients ask. First: aesthetic, Hestan is the only luxury built-in that offers the full color palette as part of the core lineup (Bordeaux burgundy, Froth sage-gray, Tin matte-gray in addition to stainless). Sub-Zero and Thermador are stainless-or-panel only. For a kitchen that wants a pop of color in the fridge plane, Hestan is it. Second: the parts chain runs through California, not Wisconsin or Germany, Anaheim direct to LA is fast. On factory parts we see 1–3 business days typically, which is faster than the Sub-Zero regional supply for some niche components. Third: chef-designed controls, Hestan's interface and feature set was developed with input from Keller and Hollingsworth and the smart-appliance integration (Hestan Cue) is more aggressive than the established competition. The trade-off: Hestan is a newer platform than Sub-Zero (established 1945) or Thermador (1916), so the multi-decade parts-support track record doesn't exist yet. For a 20-year-plus parts-availability horizon, Sub-Zero still wins; for contemporary design and California-local support, Hestan genuinely beats them."
  },
  {
    q: "Hestan has Bordeaux, Tin, Froth, if my door panel gets damaged, can you match the color?",
    a: "Yes, through the factory. Hestan's signature color finishes, Bordeaux (burgundy), Matte Black, Matte White, Froth (sage-gray), and Tin (warm gray), are factory-applied finishes on the stainless exterior substrate. Damage that requires replacing an exterior door skin means ordering the matched-finish component from Anaheim; Hestan's parts channel supports color-matched replacement panels as a standard aftermarket SKU, not a custom order. Lead times for color-matched exterior components typically run 2–4 weeks (faster than most imported-brand equivalents because the factory is in Anaheim). Our service flow: photograph the damage, confirm the exact finish code from the interior model plate, coordinate the factory-exact replacement, install when delivered. Interior-only service (gaskets, hinges, refrigeration cycle) isn't affected by the finish, same labor and parts as a stainless-finish unit."
  },
  {
    q: "What is Hestan Cue and does the refrigerator integrate with it?",
    a: "Hestan Cue is Hestan's smart-kitchen platform, originally launched for induction cooktops with a Cue-branded cookware line that pairs sensors in the pan with the cooktop for temperature-precision cooking. On the refrigerator, Hestan's smart integration is more conventional: Wi-Fi connectivity for status monitoring, temperature-setpoint alerts, door-ajar notifications, and firmware-update delivery. The refrigerator doesn't use Cue-branded pan sensors the way the cooktop does, Cue is primarily a cooking platform. Service implication on the fridge smart features: Wi-Fi association issues (the most common smart-feature service call), firmware revision for notification timing bugs on 2018–2020 units, and occasional control-board replacement when a Wi-Fi module fails independently. Firmware update $120–$180. Wi-Fi module replacement $240–$380."
  },
  {
    q: "We've got an Aspire by Hestan fridge, is that the same as Hestan for service purposes?",
    a: "Related but distinct. Aspire by Hestan is Hestan's mainstream-tier sibling brand, introduced as an approachable-price entry point while the core Hestan brand remains the luxury line. Both share the Anaheim factory and the broader Meyer Corporation backing, but product architectures differ: Aspire uses simpler control systems, more standard-spec components, and price-accessible configurations. Our techs service both platforms, parts and diagnostic tools run through the same Hestan-aftermarket channel, but the service profile on Aspire is closer to mid-premium appliance repair (think KitchenAid or GE Profile tier) than to the Hestan luxury column tier. The Aspire by Hestan lineup is a separate hub page (pending launch) on our site; this page focuses on the Hestan-branded luxury refrigeration."
  },
  {
    q: "How new is the Hestan refrigerator line? Are there long-term reliability patterns yet?",
    a: "The Hestan indoor residential refrigerator line is relatively new. Hestan launched indoor residential appliances including the column refrigerator around 2019–2020, which makes the LA installed base about 5–6 years old at maximum. Long-term failure pattern data (10+ years) doesn't exist yet, nobody has it, including Hestan. What we can report from our LA service coverage through 2025: the refrigeration side (compressor, evap, condenser, defrost) is running reliably on the 2019–2023 vintage units. The failure profile we see is concentrated on alignment-and-install issues (early commissioning era), smart-feature software (firmware-fixable), and the occasional sensor drift. No systemic compressor or sealed-system pattern has surfaced. Hestan's component-supplier choices appear solid; Meyer Corporation backing and the Anaheim manufacturing QC have produced a product that runs well in the field so far."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Hestan refrigerator repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Common Hestan bands: door gasket (column) $260–$440; door hinge re-shim and alignment $240–$420; color-matched exterior panel replacement, quoted individually (2–4 week factory lead); condenser fan motor $280–$480; evaporator fan $260–$440; defrost heater $300–$520; Hestan Cue Wi-Fi module $240–$380; firmware update $120–$180; sensor replacement $180–$340; main control board $520–$820; variable-speed compressor replacement (post-warranty) $1,100–$2,000 depending on SKU and refrigerant; ice-maker fill valve + descaling $280–$440. Because the Anaheim parts chain is fast, we often quote same-week service completion on standard parts, occasionally same-day on high-demand components. Custom color panels and niche SKUs run 2–4 weeks factory direct."
  },
  {
    q: "We bought our Hestan at a California dealer, does that help with service coordination?",
    a: "Yes, it does, and more than with most brands. Hestan's authorized dealer network in California is closely tied to the Anaheim factory operations because the retail distribution is local. If the unit is still in factory warranty, the dealer who sold the appliance usually coordinates warranty service directly through Hestan's California service channel, which runs on a tighter timeline than imported-brand warranty networks. For out-of-warranty service, or for clients who want faster-than-dealer-network response, our team handles the repair directly with genuine Hestan parts from the Anaheim aftermarket channel. Bring any purchase documentation to the first service visit; our dispatcher navigates the warranty-status check with you and determines whether factory-authorized service or our independent service is the better path."
  },
  {
    q: "Are Hestan refrigerators actually made in Anaheim, or just designed there?",
    a: "Designed, engineered, and substantially manufactured in Anaheim, with some components sourced globally, like essentially every modern appliance manufacturer. The 70,000-square-foot Anaheim facility houses the manufacturing line, the engineering team, the test kitchen, and the certified test lab. Cabinet fabrication, final assembly, factory finish application, and quality testing happen in Anaheim. Specific sub-components (compressors, circuit boards, certain sensors) are sourced from specialist manufacturers globally, this is standard industry practice and doesn't meaningfully change the \"made in California\" character of the overall product. For service, what matters is that the parts chain runs through the Anaheim operation, which is local; and the factory engineering team is accessible to our service network when a particularly tricky diagnostic case comes up. That's a genuinely different support posture than an imported luxury brand where the engineering HQ is 5,000 miles away."
  },

    {
      q: "Where can I find the official Hestan manual or warranty information?",
      a: `For official Hestan documentation, warranty registration, and authorized service locator, visit <a href="https://www.hestan.com/support/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Hestan support</a>. Our technicians work independently of Hestan's factory service network - we're often faster and available same-day in Southern California.`
    },
  ];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Hestan Refrigerator Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical,
    "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL,
    "priceRange": "$$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "Hestan Refrigerator Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Hestan refrigerator repair across Los Angeles, column built-ins in signature Bordeaux, Matte Black, Matte White, Froth, and Tin finishes, Hestan Cue smart integration, variable-speed compressor service, color-matched exterior panel replacement via Anaheim factory. California-local brand (founded 2014, Anaheim HQ, Meyer Corporation subsidiary). $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": f.q,
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a }
    }))
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Hestan", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/hestan/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Hestan Refrigerator Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <div class="call-banner">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>Hestan column fridge down? Same-day service across LA + OC:</span>
      <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
          <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Hestan › Refrigerator Repair</div>
          <h1>Hestan Refrigerator Repair</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            Hestan is the California luxury appliance brand most LA homeowners don't realize is built 45 miles down
            the freeway in Anaheim. Founded 2014 by cookware icon Stanley Cheng, backed by Meyer Corporation, with
            a 70,000-square-foot manufacturing facility in Anaheim, the same factory that makes the Hestan grills
            you see in Malibu outdoor kitchens also builds the column refrigerators we service across Beverly Hills,
            Pacific Palisades, Hollywood Hills, and Newport Coast. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic
            waived with the repair.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
            <a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="hero-facts">
            <li><b>Anaheim-local parts chain</b>, 1–3 day standard parts, 2–4 week color-matched panels</li>
            <li><b>Color-palette specialty</b>, Bordeaux, Matte Black, Matte White, Froth, Tin service protocols</li>
            <li><b>California-founded 2014</b>, Stanley Cheng, Meyer Corporation subsidiary, no offshore parent</li>
            <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
          </ul>
        </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span>
      <span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span>
      <span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Hestan in LA, the luxury brand from down the freeway</h2>
      <p>
        The fact that surprises most LA Hestan owners: their luxury refrigerator was built about 45 miles away, in
        Anaheim. Stanley Cheng, the same Stanley Cheng behind Anolon, Circulon, and a lot of the high-performance
        cookware in American kitchens, founded Hestan in 2014 with the Hestan Commercial line (chef-engineered
        professional cooking suites developed with input from Thomas Keller and Timothy Hollingsworth), expanded
        into outdoor residential grills in 2016, and launched indoor residential appliances including the column
        refrigerator around 2019–2020. The Anaheim facility houses manufacturing, engineering, the test kitchen, and
        the certified test lab, 70,000 square feet of LA-adjacent California production. The parent is Meyer
        Corporation, the US cookware conglomerate (Anolon, Circulon, Farberware, KitchenAid cookware), which is also
        California-based. That lineage is why our techs think of Hestan differently than a European-imported luxury
        brand: the product is genuinely local, the factory engineering team is accessible, and the parts chain
        doesn't cross an ocean.
      </p>
      <p>
        The LA Hestan households we serve most regularly are the ones where an outdoor-kitchen enthusiast started
        with the Hestan grill (Pacific Palisades, Malibu, Newport Coast), liked the product and the service
        experience, and upgraded the indoor kitchen to Hestan when the renovation cycle came around. Brand-family
        consistency is a bigger deal on Hestan than most brands because the color palette (Bordeaux, Matte Black,
        Matte White, Froth, Tin) carries across the grill, the range, and the refrigerator, a client who wants
        their outdoor and indoor kitchen trim finishes to match has one brand that offers it coherently. Our guys
        service both sides of the brand family, outdoor grills on the patio and column refrigerators in the kitchen
       , on the same visit when both are in scope.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Hestan refrigerator failures our techs see most often</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Pattern data from our 2019–2025 Hestan column refrigerator service coverage. The platform is newer than
        Sub-Zero or Thermador, so the long-term failure data isn't fully established, but what we see in the
        field so far is encouraging on the refrigeration side and concentrated on install-era and smart-feature
        issues.
      </p>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Door alignment and closer tension on heavy panel installs</h3>
        <p>
          Panel-ready Hestan columns installed with heavy custom-hardwood cabinet panels: when the closer tension
          wasn't adjusted at install for panel weight, the door fails to self-close fully from the factory-spec
          open angle, or the reveal gap widens at 12–18 months. Fix is closer tension adjustment plus hinge re-shim
          if the hinge has shifted. 60–90 minute service. Common on first-install units in Hollywood Hills and
          Pacific Palisades modernist homes where cabinet panels are frequently heavier than factory-assumed spec.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Color-matched exterior damage, finish preservation protocols</h3>
        <p>
          Hestan's color finishes (Bordeaux, Matte Black, Matte White, Froth, Tin) are a signature feature and need
          careful handling. Scratches or dents on the factory finish from a move, a cabinet install, or a kitchen
          renovation require factory-color-matched replacement panels. Lead time on color-matched exterior components
          from the Anaheim factory is typically 2–4 weeks (faster than imported-brand equivalents). Our protocol:
          document the damage, confirm the exact finish code from the interior model plate, coordinate the
          replacement order, install when delivered. Interior service on a color-finish unit (gaskets, hinges,
          refrigeration cycle) runs identical to stainless-finish labor.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Hestan Cue Wi-Fi / smart-feature issues</h3>
        <p>
          Smart-feature complaints on 2018–2022 Hestan refrigerators almost always trace back to Wi-Fi association
          failures or firmware revisions. Our guys run the Hestan Cue firmware update first (resolves a good share
          of notification-delivery bugs on early units), then diagnose the Wi-Fi module if the symptom persists.
          Firmware update $120–$180. Wi-Fi module replacement $240–$380. Refrigeration cycle itself is usually
          fine when smart features misbehave, the symptom looks serious but the fix is software-side.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Ice-maker mineral buildup, LA hard-water pattern</h3>
        <p>
          Ice production drops progressively over 6–12 months on Hestan column refrigerators in Encino, Sherman
          Oaks, Tarzana, Calabasas, and Pasadena, LA's harder-water neighborhoods. Standard descaling plus fill-
          valve inspection and replacement where needed. Service $280–$440. Annual descaling recommended for
          heavy-ice-production households. Hestan's ice-maker architecture is a standard module (shared
          component-class with several other luxury brands), so parts availability is good.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Sensor drift on early multi-zone architectures</h3>
        <p>
          A subset of 2019–2020 Hestan columns had occasional zone-sensor drift producing temperature misread in
          one compartment without the compressor sounding wrong. Diagnostic: read zone sensors through Hestan's
          service interface, verify against calibrated probe, replace drifted sensor. Sensor service $180–$340.
          Post-2021 units appear to have improved sensor calibration out of the factory; we haven't seen the drift
          pattern on newer vintage as frequently.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Refrigeration cycle, running solid so far</h3>
        <p>
          Honest note on compressor, evaporator, condenser, and defrost performance: we haven't seen significant
          systemic failure patterns on Hestan columns through 5 years of LA field coverage. Compressor noise is
          within spec, temperature holds are stable, defrost cycles complete correctly. Hestan's component choices
          and QC out of Anaheim appear solid. Long-term (10+ years) data obviously doesn't exist yet for any
          Hestan refrigerator; we'll update this section as the field data matures.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Hestan US refrigerator lines we service</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        The Hestan residential refrigeration lineup is column-focused with signature color finish options unique in
        the luxury category. Built in Anaheim, CA with Meyer Corporation backing.
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>36" Column Refrigerator</h3>
          <p>Flagship built-in column. Panel-ready or in signature Hestan finishes (Bordeaux, Matte Black, Matte
          White, Froth, Tin) plus stainless. Variable-speed compressor, multi-zone cooling, Hestan Cue Wi-Fi
          connectivity. Direct spec competitor to Sub-Zero 648PRO and Thermador Freedom column at similar price
          point.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>30" Column Refrigerator</h3>
          <p>Narrower column variant for smaller kitchens or column-pair installs. Same architecture and color
          options as the 36". Common in Westside condos and pantry integrations in Hollywood Hills renovation
          projects.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Column freezers (matched)</h3>
          <p>24" and 30" freezer columns matched to refrigerator columns for paired installs. Same design language,
          same hardware trim options, same service profile. Ice-maker integration on select configurations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Panel-ready configurations</h3>
          <p>All Hestan columns accept cabinet-panel integration. Eliminates the stainless or color finish from the
          factory exterior; cabinet maker supplies the visible face. Common spec for Silver Lake modernist kitchens
          and custom hillside homes where the fridge disappears into cabinetry.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Bordeaux / Matte / Froth / Tin color finishes</h3>
          <p>Hestan's signature color palette. Factory-applied finishes on the stainless substrate, color-matched
          trim hardware options (handle finishes: Bronze, Brushed Stainless, Tin, Froth). Color-matched exterior
          panel replacement available through Anaheim factory with 2–4 week typical lead time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Hestan Cue smart integration</h3>
          <p>Wi-Fi-enabled platform, status monitoring, temperature alerts, door-ajar notifications, remote
          setpoint adjustment, firmware updates over the air. Smart features are helpful but not mission-critical;
          the refrigeration cycle doesn't depend on Cue connectivity.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Hestan vs Sub-Zero vs Thermador, the LA-local luxury column conversation</h2>
      <p>
        Three luxury column brands our clients most often consider against Hestan: Sub-Zero, Thermador, and
        occasionally BlueStar on the American-made side. We don't sell appliances so we don't have a commercial
        stake, but here's the honest read our techs describe from the field.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Sub-Zero</b>, Wisconsin-built, Bakke family since 1945, strongest LA parts chain. Longest legacy
        support. Stainless-or-panel only (no color options). Most conservative aesthetic. See
        <a href="/brands/sub-zero-refrigerator-repair/">Sub-Zero refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Thermador</b>, BSH's luxury column (Freedom Collection). Shared parts chain with Bosch. Strong column-
        width flexibility and refrigeration drawers. See
        <a href="/brands/thermador-refrigerator-repair/">Thermador refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Hestan</b>, California-local, Anaheim-manufactured since 2014, Meyer Corporation backing. Signature
        color palette (the only luxury built-in brand offering Bordeaux, Froth, Tin, Matte Black, Matte White
        finishes as standard). Hestan Cue smart integration. Fastest California parts chain, Anaheim direct to
        LA runs 1–3 days on standard parts. The newest platform in the category, so 10-plus-year field data is
        still accumulating but early signals are positive. Best pick when color aesthetics matter, when the
        household already has a Hestan outdoor grill, or when "California-made" is a meaningful differentiator.
      </p>
      <p>
        None is objectively better, they're positioned differently. For a 20-year parts-horizon commitment,
        Sub-Zero still wins. For design-forward color options and California-local support, Hestan is genuinely
        the leader. Our team services all three with identical care and training.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>What Hestan refrigerator repair typically costs</h2>
      <p class="intro">Parts pricing is in line with other luxury column brands; lead times run faster than
      imported competitors because the Anaheim factory is local. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
      <table class="price-table">
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Flat, waived if repair is authorized same visit</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door closer tension adjustment</td><td>$120 – $240</td><td>Panel-weight rebalance</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door hinge re-shim and alignment</td><td>$240 – $420</td><td>Hestan offset gauge, panel-weight adjusted</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket replacement (column)</td><td>$260 – $440</td><td>Factory parts, Anaheim direct</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Zone sensor replacement</td><td>$180 – $340</td><td>Hestan service interface diagnostic</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Hestan Cue firmware update</td><td>$120 – $180</td><td>Resolves most Wi-Fi / notification issues</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Hestan Cue Wi-Fi module</td><td>$240 – $380</td><td>When firmware doesn't resolve</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Condenser fan motor replacement</td><td>$280 – $480</td><td>Common column specs on truck</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Evaporator fan / defrost heater</td><td>$260 – $520</td><td>Defrost cycle faults</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ice-maker fill valve + descaling</td><td>$280 – $440</td><td>Hard-water LA households</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Main control board replacement</td><td>$520 – $820</td><td>After firmware and diagnosis</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Variable-speed compressor (post-warranty)</td><td>$1,100 – $2,000</td><td>Anaheim parts chain direct</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Color-matched exterior panel</td><td>Quoted individually</td><td>2–4 week factory lead time</td></tr>
      </table>
      <p class="small">
